article.headline: Davidson 50, Butler 10
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) -- Ryan Alexander passed for 347 yards and completed 22-of-33 passes on his way to setting to two school records as Davidson routed Butler 50-10 on Saturday. Alexander added 37 yards on two carries for the Wildcats (6-4, 5-2 Pioneer). His season passing total of 2,681 yards and 2,766 total yards broke Davidson records set by Gordon Slade in 1969. Brett Dioguardi caught four passes for 80 yards to became the Wildcats' all-time receiving leader with a career total of 2,215 receiving yards. He surpassed the 2,157 mark set by former teammate Barrett Johnson. Ryan Hubbard caught eight passes for 189 yards and two scores. His brother, Jonathon, had 87 yards on 23 carries and two touchdowns. Butler (3-8, 2-5) scored its only touchdown on a four-yard run by Derek North midway through the fourth quarter. Ryan Diggins completed 17-of-32 passes for 139 yards. Butler was held to just 233 yards on offense. Davidson amassed a season-high 560 yards, its third most in the past 25 seasons.
